            .</p>
               <p>WILLIAM COWIE. I pawned things for my mother in that name sometimes.</p>
               <p>GEORGE AVIS. I took the prisoner on the 26th of May - he said he picked it up on the stairs at the house to which he belonged, and he did not know whose it was.</p>
               <p>MR. WRIGHT. This is my handkerchief - it could not<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183106300048"></xptr>have fallen on the stairs - it had been in a particular drawer in my bed-room.</p>
